text: Esther Cordus (born 14 August 1994) is a Dutch korfball player. She is a member of KZ/Hiltex and the Netherlands national korfball team. With the national team she made her debut at the 2017 World Games where she won the gold medal. She became again champion at the 2022 World Games in Birmingham, Alabama. ==Achievements== ===Club=== *Korfball Europa Cup champion, 1x (2013) * champion, 1x (2015) * champion, 1x (2014) ===National team=== *World Games champion, 2x (2017, 2022) *World champion, 1x (2019) *European champion, 2x (2018, 2021) ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch korfball players Category:Sportspeople from Zaanstad Category:Sportswomen
